From: hejuworld-droid <hejuworld-droid@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 22 May 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] AN400: Change boot order to SD card first

The default boot order tries eMMC first, which causes hang if eMMC
has no valid system. Change to SD card first for Armbian installation.

This patch modifies kvim4.h to prioritize SD card boot.
---
 board/khadas/configs/kvim4.h | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/board/khadas/configs/kvim4.h b/board/khadas/configs/kvim4.h
index 626f7d37..cccccccc 100644
--- a/board/khadas/configs/kvim4.h
+++ b/board/khadas/configs/kvim4.h
@@ -76,9 +76,9 @@
 #endif
 #ifndef BOOT_TARGET_DEVICES
 #define BOOT_TARGET_DEVICES(func) \
     BOOT_TARGET_DEVICES_USB(func) \
-    func(MMC, mmc, 0) \
     func(MMC, mmc, 1) \
+    func(MMC, mmc, 0) \
     func(PXE, pxe, na) \
     func(DHCP, dhcp, na)
 #endif
-- 
